fields.description:
With the implementation of Atlassian Account across Service Desk, Portal Desk customers must now use their designated portal URLs instead of being able to use the instance base URL. Before this implementation, customers could visit a base URL ex. instancename.atlassian.net and enter their portal credentials, where they would be redirected to their customer portal menu.

This change can be problematic for existing service desk users, as customers to service desks might not have their specific portal urls. I believe that we should implement the ability to use the base URLs for portal customers who are now using Atlassian Account.
fields.summary: Atlassian Account Service Desk Portal URL

fields.description:
h3. Problem Definition
Currently if an issue is moved from a SD project and the users have a saved URL like: 
https://instance-name.atlassian.net/projects/CS/queues/custom/161/CS-23588. 
when accesing this link it points to all issues: https://instance-name.atlassian.net/projects/NEW/issues/NEW-549?filter=allopenissues

h3. Suggested Solution
The link should point to the issue in the new project where it was moved

 
h3. Workaround 
Users can save issues in the format https://instance-name.atlassian.net/browse/CS-23588, which will redirect correctly to the issue where it was moved https://instance-name.atlassian.net/browse/NEW-23588
fields.summary: A link from a SD queue of an issue should redirect to the issue in the new project where it was moved

fields.description:
h3. Summary
Viewing or accessing attachments within JIRA or Confluence Cloud on Internet Explorer 11.x is returning the error:
{quote}
"Ouch! We can't load the PDF.
/secure/attachment/..pdf
{quote}

h3. Steps to replicate
# Open Issue with PDF attached or a Confluence page with an attachments linked, with Internet Explorer 11.x
# Click on to display the PDF preview

h3. Expected Result
- Able to preview the PDF within the browser

h3. Actual Result
Unable to generate the PDF preview
Error "Ouch! We can't load the PDF as per attached image:
 !image013.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Workaround
# Go to Internet options
# Go to Security tab
# Click on Internet Icon and click on Custom Level
# Scroll to the middle of the Security Settings, under Miscellaneous, enable "Access data sources across domain"
fields.summary: Ouch! We can't load the PDF on IE11

fields.description:
h3. Summary
When a user pastes a link that contains parenthesis in the Description field in JIRA, it stays blacked out and the link does not work properly.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
Paste a link into the JIRA description field and it has a parenthesis.
The parenthesis gets blacked out and the link does not work properly

h3. Expected Results
Click on the link and it opens normally even within a parenthesis in the middle of it.

h3. Notes
This problem only happens in the description field. 
Trying on comments, and the parenthesis in the link do not get blacked out and the link works normally.

h3.Workaround
Paste the link between " [ ] "
fields.summary: Parenthesis blacked out and link does not work

fields.description:
We build with the build numbers following the bambooBuildNumber to label each release.  We don't always deploy every release as its made, so sometimes our releases skip over a build result.  We are finding it hard to go back and resurrect a release that was never made into a release; the dropdown picker does not allow that as a choice.

 

We would like to be able to go back to older build results and create releases after they are superseded to verify when a  bug we just now noticed crept into the build.
fields.summary: Creating releases from previous build results

fields.description:
h3. Problem Definition

1. In any wiki markup enabled editor, write a few words.
 2. Select one word and click on the *link* button, choose *External link*.
 3. The correct markup will appear like {{[selected_text|example.com]}}.

Your selected word will still be highlighted, so if you now paste your link URL, it will appear like this {{[your_URL_pastes_here|example.com]}}.
h3. Suggested Solution

The example URL should be pre-selected instead, so that on a paste, it should appear {{[selected_text|your_URL_pastes_here]}}.
fields.summary: Improvement for 'External link' link macro in the JIRA editor

fields.description:
h3. Problem Definition
Before, files used always to download when links were clicked (from an issue or from a .csv export file). Now, some files are being opened as a browser preview when the link is hit instead of downloading.

Tested file extensions with this behavior so far:

.txt
.csv
.html


h3. Suggested Solution
Make files download instead of opening in a browser preview which is also not editable.
fields.summary: JIRA Cloud Media API open some files in browser preview instead of downloading

fields.description:
When I have started entering a comment, don't - EVER - automatically refresh the JIRA board and loose everything I have typed.

This doesn't happen while actively typing, perhaps because I see the warning and tell it not to refresh. But if I go look at information in another window, sometimes when I come back (seconds or minutes later), I find my comment gone. How is that possibly good U/X?

User agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_12_1) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/54.0.2840.98 Safari/537.36

Initial report: [https://support.atlassian.com/servicedesk/agent/JST/issue/JST-243448]
fields.summary: Don't refresh board while entering a comment

fields.description: rdesa adsadsa dad a da d a

You have a Cloud instance with JIRA and Confluence.

Confluence is set as the main landing page of your instance.

If you are a logged user and access your instance main url address (ex: domain.atlassian.net), you will be redirected to Confluence.

If you have public spaces, access your instance main url address (ex: domain.atlassian.net) as an anonymous user, you will be asked to autenticate because the application will think that you are trying to access JIRA instead of redirect you to the Confluence page with the public spaces.

Anonymous users should also be redirect to Confluence whenever Confluence is set as the main landing page when accessing the instance main url address.
fields.summary: Landing page should also affect anonymous users.

See a plain text file

h3. Actual Results
A html processed code

h3.Workaround
Download the file and open elsewhere

fields.description:
According to [this password security documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/manage-password-security-794198948.html], there's a few items to be updated, according to the Cloud instances structure. For example:

 
 # In the first line to *enable a password policy*, it says "*Select **!https://confluence.atlassian.com/download/thumbnails/749382612/cog.png?version=1&modificationDate=1441861388789&api=v2|width=30! **> Security*.", but, this is not how we do it in Cloud, and the *Security* option does not exist in the cog icon. It should "Select *!https://confluence.atlassian.com/download/thumbnails/749382612/cog.png?version=1&modificationDate=1441861388789&api=v2|width=30!  > User Management > Password Policy*"
 # In the *Set 'Custom' password settings* session, it will state that we have the option to update specific fields: *Password Length, **Character Variety, **Similarity Checks. *However, by going to the Password Policy in Cloud, these fields do not exist. These are only methods on how the user will measure the customisation for the password. We should update it, so it can avoid confusion while people are looking for those fields.
 # The *Similarity checks for 'Custom' password settings* session is about a field that does not exist, as mentioned in the item above. Also, it could provide some additional confusion since it states that we have the *Ignored*, *Lenient*, or *Strict *options to set. We could remove this part, since in the topic above, we will be clarifying that these are only methods for measuring the password complexity/strength

 

A correct documentation, with the available information on the password policy can be found through [this link|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/set-password-requirements-744721633.html].
fields.summary: Update Password Security Documentation for Cloud
